    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - FRONT DRIVE AXLE: SPICER S-9000 - REMOVAL OF DIFFERENTIAL FROM CARRIER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>REMOVAL OF DIFFERENTIAL FROM CARRIER</title>
        <para>Use
            <hotlnk document="s02009_9.xml" xrefid="f0200903">Figure 3</hotlnk>
            as a reference to remove the differential from the carrier.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cotter pins and locks from bearing caps (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200904">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200904" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200904" filename="../figg02/G0200904.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Remove Cotter Pins</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Match mark one differential bearing cap and leg of carrier with center punch or chisel for
                correct reassembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200905">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200905" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200905" filename="../figg02/G0200905.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Match Mark For Correct Reassembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four (4) bearing cap retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200906">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200906" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200906" filename="../figg02/G0200906.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Remove Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing caps.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove adjusting rings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lift the ring gear and differential subassembly out of carrier (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200907">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200907" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200907" filename="../figg02/G0200907.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Lift Out of Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The ring gear side of sub-assembly must be tipped up for the ring gear to clear pinion roller
                        bearing retainer.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use care to avoid damage to ring and pinion gears. If either is damaged, it must be replaced
                        as part of a matched set.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
